article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 99, Schreiner 54
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Matt Kingsley scored a career-high 30 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 99-54 victory over Schreiner on Tuesday night. Trevor Guy added 17 points and had seven rebounds for Stephen F. Austin (2-2). The Lumberjacks also made 47 points off Schreiner's 33 turnovers. Kevin Deans led Schreiner (0-3) with 14 points. He was Schreiner's only player in double figures. The Lumberjacks led 44-30 at the half. Stephen F. Austin shot 62 percent from the field to 43 percent for Schreiner.
